context: The word 'saabus' is the past tense form of the Estonian verb 'saabuma', which means to arrive or come. It indicates that someone or something has arrived at a destination in the past. In the given context from the dictionary definition, it shows how hundreds of journalists (radio, TV and newspaper men) arrived for major competitions.
